	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=48926><span id=Scholar>willherr</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>19 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>They're saying that because they have no good idea of how to best utilize a ranger in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;Chalk it up to poor tactical knowledge and get with a group that has an idea of how to use the different classes.<br><br>Rangers are great group classes.  Warriors may be able to dish out damage, but when it comes right down to it our spells can out-taunt them every time.  Clerics can heal, but how many can dish out crit hits with a projectile weapon?  Int casters can dish damage and crowd control, but they can't handle damage close in.<br><br>In a nutshell, there is no worst class.  Just worst players.  If you want a good group, experiment with the different ways to handle mobs and don't limit yourself to being a tank or a healer.  You'll find that good groups will be falling over themselves to get you in as soon as word gets around that you know your stuff.<br><br><br>Case in point:  at 16 I was fighting in BlackBurrow with a 17 Cleric.  We pulled the upstairs commander room and pulled 5 mobs including a named splitpaw.  At the outset of the battle an Iksar monk showed up and asked if we needed help, and we said 'naw, we got it covered'.  I ran myself out of mana with Invoke Lightning and Snare before the fight was half over, but we came out of it exceptionally well.<br><br>He waited until the end of the fight before he left.  When I sent him a tell thanking him for standing by in case we needed help, he responded 'no, I was just standing there watching, in awe of the fact that you were able to cast and maintain aggro on all 5 of those mobs while she was dropping heals on you left and right'.  <br><br>A ranger who knows how to play a ranger is an asset to any group.  A ranger who tries to play like a different class will generally have a much tougher time and be more of a liability to a group.  End of story.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
