	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=10&mid=99486142735291>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=10&mid=99486142735291>RE: Bad class?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=10&mid=99486142735291#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 11th 10:23 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39735><span id= >spaten</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>GO RANGERS!<br><br>Nice post.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ranger's do have it tough.  There are many non-ranger types out there that have no idea of our abilities.  Unfortunately, you often need to be grouped to really "practice" being a good Ranger and, yes, you will make mistakes along the way but, that's what the game's about.  I thought I'd add in a couple of Ranger tips that most other classes can't get away with.<br><br>1.  Kitting with your bow:  as soon as you get them, scribe Ensnaring Roots, Snare and whatever flame spell you can get.  After a little practice, you can solo yellows and, I've even seen a couple Rangers that will take on reds with this tactic.  When you engage the mob, be sure to snare first.  Until you've had a LOT of practice, the mob stands a very good chance of saving against your root spell.  With the mob snared, you can rain arrows down on them while walking backwards or in a large circle.  Stop occasionally and attempt to cast root.  If you root the mob, you can alternate between arrow and flame spell.  Do this until you're out of mana and/or arrows and then engage in melee!<br><br>2.  Bow Hunting - Most non-rangers will tell you this can't be done.  They are wrong.  As you can see above, it's a very good tactic and quite common among solo'ing rangers.  At lower levels (below 17) and with the right bow, rangers are even more effective than warriors!  Here's how :)  Get a Trueshot Longbow.  You can do the quest (recommended) or you can opt to buy one for about 150pp.  These are great bows and they're only for us rangers!  The stas on the TS are 20dmg/45dly/100rng (.444 ratio).  This allows you to stand away from the mob while still hitting it harder and/or faster than the warrior!  If your warrior isn't twinked, it's doubtfull he will have a sword with a better ratio :)  The down side to this is that the uneducated don't "see" you attacking the mob and assume you're just sitting back and rakin' in the exp at everone else's expense.  They usually keep up that attitude until they start seeing your critical hits :)  Also, once you get dual weild (lvl 17, right?) you can probably get a better ratio by using two melee weapons... but, there are even better bows out there!<br><br>Good luck young Rangers!<br>Spaten Optimator<br>Lanys T'Vyl</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
